# HyBBX project rules

Read [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) and [docs/DEVELOPMENT.md](../../docs/DEVELOPMENT.md) for full context.

## Product

- Arch: centralized daemon + link/repeater edge ([docs/ROADMAP.md](../../docs/ROADMAP.md), `share/hybbx.ini.example`).
- **0.5.x** line — no `docs/RELEASE-*` files until v1.0.0; use [docs/FEATURES.md](../../docs/FEATURES.md) and [docs/ROADMAP.md](../../docs/ROADMAP.md).
- **HyBBX uses a centralized daemon and link/repeater daemon technologies to expand networks, range, and features** ([docs/ROADMAP.md](../../docs/ROADMAP.md)).

## Code

- C99, `hybbx_` prefix, `hybbx_result_t` for errors.
- Core (`src/core/`) = sessions + HBX/TCP circuit only — **no KISS/AX.25/telnet parsing** in core.
- Link adapters live in `plugins/`.
- Booleans: `hybbx_parse_bool()` — yes/no + standard aliases ([include/hybbx/util.h](../../include/hybbx/util.h)).
- Minimal scope; match existing style; respect [include/hybbx/limits.h](../../include/hybbx/limits.h).

## Docs

- Update [docs/FEATURES.md](../../docs/FEATURES.md) when changing functionality.
- Config changes → [docs/MANUAL.md](../../docs/MANUAL.md) + `share/hybbx.ini.example`.

## Git

- Public commits: `user.name=ngteq`, empty `user.email`, **no** `Co-authored-by` agent lines.
- Do not commit or push unless the user asks.
